h3cCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSClassifierCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Classifier configuration information.

h3cCBQoSClassifierIndex.name: h3cCBQoSClassifierIndex
h3cCBQoSClassifierIndex.description: Index of Traffic Classifier. Begin with 0.

h3cCBQoSClassifierRuleCount.name: h3cCBQoSClassifierRuleCount
h3cCBQoSClassifierRuleCount.description: The counter of match rules of Traffic classifier.

h3cCBQoSClassifierOperator.name: h3cCBQoSClassifierOperator
h3cCBQoSClassifierOperator.description: Operator of the match rules of traffic classifier. Software QoS supports and, or. Hardware QoS supports and.

h3cCBQoSClassifierLayer.name: h3cCBQoSClassifierLayer
h3cCBQoSClassifierLayer.description: Configuration layer of traffic classifier. Only hardware QoS support it. 1(unavailable) is returned only when getting value from software QoS. 1(unavailable) can't be set.

h3cCBQosClassifierMatchRuleNextIndex.name: h3cCBQosClassifierMatchRuleNextIndex
h3cCBQosClassifierMatchRuleNextIndex.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIndex when creating rows in the h3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable. Begin with 0. If the value of this node is 65535, it indicates creating a row in h3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable is not permitted.

h3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSMatchRuleCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Match Rule configuration information.

h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.name: h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot
h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIfNot.description: Whether the if-match rule is a match or matchNot statement. Software QoS supports match, matchNot. Hardware QoS supports match.

h3cCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.name: h3cCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue
h3cCBQoSMatchRuleStringValue.description: Value of Match Rule. SourceMAC: SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match source-mac 0101-0202-0303' DestinationMAC: SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match destination-mac 0101-0202-0303' Classifier: SIZE (1..31) classifier name InboundInterface: SIZE (1..47) interface description TopMostVlanID, VlanID:SIZE(1..39), up to 8 value can be input; for example: 1#11#111#1111 means the match rule if 'if-match vlanid 1 11 111 1111' SourceIp: SIZE (12) HHHHHHHHHHHH for example: 010102020303 means the match rule is 'if-match source-ip mac-address 0101-0202-0303' other types: Set is not permitted. Zero-length String will be returned when getting.

h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.name: h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1
h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1.description: Value of Match Rule. IPv4 ACL: 2000~5999 IPv6 ACL: 2000~3999; 10000~42767 Software QoS: 2000~3999 Hardware Qos: 10000~42767 RtpPort: start-port: 2000~65535 IpPrec: value: 0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match ip-prec 0 1 4 6' Dscp: value:0~63,up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 32~63. The bit set to 1 of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2 is used to indicate the value 0~31. for example: 0x80000003 means the match rule is 'if-match dscp 32 33 63' Vlan8021p: value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match customer-dot1p 0 1 4 6' MplsExp: value:0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the 8 value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match mpls 0 1 4 6' SourceIp: 1~4095 QosLocalID: 1~4095 AtmClp: 0~1 FrDe: 0~1 LocalPrecedence: 0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match localprecedence 0 1 4 6' DropPriority: 0~2, up to 3 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 3 bits of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~2. ServiceDot1p: 0~7, up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of the last 8 bits of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 0~7. for example: 0x53(Binary format is 01010011) means the match rule is 'if-match service-dot1p 0 1 4 6' other types: Set is not permitted. 0xffffffff will be returned when getting.

h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.name: h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2
h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2.description: Value of Match Rule. RtpPort(3): end-port: 2000~65535 Dscp(6): value:0~63,up to 8 value can be input. The bit set to 1 of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue1 is used to indicate the value 32~63. The bit set to 1 of h3cCBQoSMatchRuleIntValue2 is used to indicate the value 0~31. for example: 0x80000003 means the match rule is 'if-match dscp 0 1 31' other types: Set is not permitted. 0xffffffff will be returned when getting.

h3cCBQoSMatchIpAddressType.name: h3cCBQoSMatchIpAddressType
h3cCBQoSMatchIpAddressType.description: A value that represents a type of Internet address. unknown(0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address which is not in one of the formats defined below. ipv4(1) An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention. ipv6(2) A global IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention. ipv4z(3) A non-global IPv4 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv4z textual convention. ipv6z(4) A non-global IPv6 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv6z textual convention. dns(16) A DNS domain name as defined by the InetAddressDNS textual convention. Value of match rule. SourceIp support this node. other types: Set is not permitted. Unknown will be returned when getting.

h3cCBQoSMatchIpAddress.name: h3cCBQoSMatchIpAddress
h3cCBQoSMatchIpAddress.description: Denotes a generic Internet address. SourceIP support this node. other types: Set is not permitted. NULL will be returned when getting.

h3cCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext.name: h3cCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext
h3cCBQoSBehaviorIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for h3cCBQoSBehaviorIndex when creating rows in the h3cCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.

h3cCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSBehaviorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Traffic Behavior configuration information.

h3cCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSCarCfgInfoTable.description: A table of CAR feature configuration information.

h3cCBQoSCarEbs.name: h3cCBQoSCarEbs
h3cCBQoSCarEbs.description: Excess Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only software QoS support this node. 4294967295 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS. 4294967295 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSCarPir.name: h3cCBQoSCarPir
h3cCBQoSCarPir.description: Peak Information Rate. Unit: kbps. Only hardware QoS support this node. 4294967295 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. 4294967295 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSCarPbs.name: h3cCBQoSCarPbs
h3cCBQoSCarPbs.description: Peak Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only hardware QoS support this node. 4294967295 is returned only when getting value from software QoS. 4294967295 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSCarGreenAction.name: h3cCBQoSCarGreenAction
h3cCBQoSCarGreenAction.description: Green Action Hardware QoS : pass, discard, remark. Software QoS : pass, discard, remark IP Precedence, remark DSCP, remark MPLS EXP.

h3cCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.name: h3cCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue
h3cCBQoSCarGreenRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When green action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. 255 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass,discard of software QoS. 255 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSCarYellowAction.name: h3cCBQoSCarYellowAction
h3cCBQoSCarYellowAction.description: Yellow Action: Only hardware QoS support this node. Hardware QoS support pass, discard, remark. invalid is returned only when getting value from software QoS. invalid can't be set.

h3cCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue.name: h3cCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue
h3cCBQoSCarYellowRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When red action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. 255 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass, discard of software QoS. 255 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSCarRedAction.name: h3cCBQoSCarRedAction
h3cCBQoSCarRedAction.description: Red Action: Hardware QoS : pass, discard, remark. Software QoS : pass, discard, remark IP Precedence, remark DSCP, remark MPLS EXP.

h3cCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.name: h3cCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue
h3cCBQoSCarRedRemarkValue.description: The value is to remark When red action is remarking. For remarking DSCP, the range is 0~63; For remarking IP Precedence and MPLS EXP, the range is 0~7; Only software QoS support this node. 255 is returned only when getting value from hardware QoS or when action being pass, discard of software QoS. 255 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoTable.description: A table of aggregative CAR applied CBQ feature configuration information. Aggregative CAR is managed by H3C-IFQOS2-MIB. So, you can use H3C-IFQOS2-MIB to get some details information about aggregative CAR.

h3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoEntry.name: h3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoEntry
h3cCBQoSAggregativeCarCfgInfoEntry.description: Aggregative CAR feature applied CBQ configuration information entry.

h3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarIndex.name: h3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarIndex
h3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarIndex.description: Index of aggregative CAR. It is equal to h3cIfQoSAggregativeCarIndex at H3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

h3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarName.name: h3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarName
h3cCBQoSCarAggregativeCarName.description: Name of aggregative CAR. It is equal to h3cIfQoSAggregativeCarName at H3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

h3cCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSGtsCfgInfoTable.description: A table of GTS feature configuration information.

h3cCBQoSGtsCbs.name: h3cCBQoSGtsCbs
h3cCBQoSGtsCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte default: max(cir*1/2,15000)

h3cCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSRemarkCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Remarking feature configuration information.

h3cCBQoSRemarkValue.name: h3cCBQoSRemarkValue
h3cCBQoSRemarkValue.description: Value to remark: for IpPrecedence: 0~7 for Dscp: 0~63 for MplsExp: 0~7 for Vlan8021p: 0~7 for AtmClp: 0~1 for FrDe: 0~1 for VlanID: 1~4094 for QosLocalID: 1~4095 for DropPrecedence: 0~2 for LocalPrecedence: 0~7 for TopMostVlanID: 1~4094

h3cCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSQueueCfgInfoTable.description: A table of queue feature configuration information.

h3cCBQoSQueueDropType.name: h3cCBQoSQueueDropType
h3cCBQoSQueueDropType.description: The drop type of queue. Only valid for AF and WFQ queue. typeUnavailable is returned only when getting value about EF queue. typeUnavailable can't be set.

h3cCBQoSQueueLength.name: h3cCBQoSQueueLength
h3cCBQoSQueueLength.description: The length of QueueLength. Only valid for tail-drop type of AF and WFQ queue. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about EF queue or WRED type of AF and WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.name: h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit
h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthUnit.description: Bandwidth Unit: Absolute, Unit Kbps (1) Percent, Unit % (2) Only valid for EF and AF queue. 0 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. 0 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.name: h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue
h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue.description: Bandwidth value: Absolute value: 8~10000000. Unit: Kbps Percent value: 1~100. Only valid for EF and AF queue. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSQueueCbs.name: h3cCBQoSQueueCbs
h3cCBQoSQueueCbs.description: Committed Burst Size. Unit: byte. Only valid for EF queue. Default: If the value of 'h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25' is between 1500 and 2000000, the default value of this object is 'h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25';If the value of 'h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25' is larger than or equal to 2000000, the default value of this object is 2000000; If the value of 'h3cCBQoSQueueBandwidthValue * 25' is less than or equal to 1500, the default value of this object is 1500. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.name: h3cCBQoSQueueQueueNumber
h3cCBQoSQueueQueueNumber.description: Max number of hashed queues (a power of 2). Only valid for WFQ. 'unavailable' is returned only when getting value about AF or EF queue. 'unavailable' can't be set.

h3cCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.name: h3cCBQoSQueueCbsRatio
h3cCBQoSQueueCbsRatio.description: Committed Burst Size Ratio. CBS = CBS_Ratio * Bandwidth(k bps) Only valid for EF queue. 2147483647 is returned only when getting value about AF or WFQ queue. 2147483647 can't be set.

h3cCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSWredCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

h3cCBQoSWredWeightConst.name: h3cCBQoSWredWeightConst
h3cCBQoSWredWeightConst.description: Specify weight for calculating mean queue depth.

h3cCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSWredClassCfgInfoTable.description: A table of WRED configuration information.

h3cCBQoSWredClassValue.name: h3cCBQoSWredClassValue
h3cCBQoSWredClassValue.description: The class value. For IP precedence based WRED, the class is IP precedence, and range is 0~7. For DSCP based WRED, the class is DSCP, and range is 0~63.

h3cCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.name: h3cCBQoSWredClassLowLimit
h3cCBQoSWredClassLowLimit.description: The low limit of queue depth.

h3cCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.name: h3cCBQoSWredClassHighLimit
h3cCBQoSWredClassHighLimit.description: The high limit of queue depth.

h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Policy Routing configuration information.

h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop.name: h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop
h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteNexthop.description: The next-hop ip address for redirection.

h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup.name: h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup
h3cCBQoSPolicyRouteBackup.description: Whether forward the packet according to the routing table When the next-hop IP address for redirection is not valid. Backup means forwarding. NoBackup means not forwarding.

h3cCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSNatCfgInfoTable.description: A table of Nat configuration information.

h3cCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSFirewallCfgInfoTable.description: A table of firewall configuration information.

h3cCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSSamplingCfgInfoTable.description: A table of sampling configuration information.

h3cCBQoSAccountCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSAccountCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSAccountCfgInfoTable.description: A table of account configuration information.

h3cCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSRedirectCfgInfoTable.description: A table of redirect configuration information.

h3cCBQoSRedirectIfIndex.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectIfIndex
h3cCBQoSRedirectIfIndex.description: ifIndex. Only the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectType is interface, can be set this node.

h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType
h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType.description: A value that represents a type of Internet address. unknown(0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address which is not in one of the formats defined below. ipv4(1) An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention. ipv6(2) A global IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention. ipv4z(3) A non-global IPv4 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv4z textual convention. ipv6z(4) A non-global IPv6 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv6z textual convention. dns(16) A DNS domain name as defined by the InetAddressDNS textual convention. Now supports ipv4 and ipv6. Only the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectType is next-hop, can be set this node and h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1 or h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2.

h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1
h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1.description: IP Address. If the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectType is not next-hop, Zero-length String will be returned when getting. If the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6, this node is set necessarily.

h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2
h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2.description: IP Address. If the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectType is not next-hop, Zero-length String will be returned when getting. If the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6, this node is set optionally.

h3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface1.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface1
h3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface1.description: IfIndex for ipv6 next hop . If and only if the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6 and h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress1 is set, this node can be set.

h3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface2.name: h3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface2
h3cCBQoSRedirectIpv6Interface2.description: IfIndex for ipv6 next hop . If and only if the value of h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddressType is ipv6 and h3cCBQoSRedirectIpAddress2 is set, this node can be set.

h3cCBQoSPriorityMapCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSPriorityMapCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSPriorityMapCfgInfoTable.description: A table of priority map configuration information.

h3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupIndex.name: h3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupIndex
h3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupIndex.description: Index of map group. Map group is managed by H3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

h3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupName.name: h3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupName
h3cCBQoSPriorityMapGroupName.description: Name of map group. Map group is managed by H3C-IFQOS2-MIB.

h3cCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSMirrorCfgInfoTable.description: A table of flow mirror configuration information.

h3cCBQoSMirrorIfIndex.name: h3cCBQoSMirrorIfIndex
h3cCBQoSMirrorIfIndex.description: IfIndex of destination interface. Only the value of h3cCBQoSMirrorType is interface, can be set this node. For example: 1#11#111#1111 means the flow mirror destination ifindex is 1,11,111 and 1111. '#' is list separator for all IfIndex value.

h3cCBQoSMirrorVlanID.name: h3cCBQoSMirrorVlanID
h3cCBQoSMirrorVlanID.description: Destination vlan of flow mirror, Only the value of h3cCBQoSMirrorType is vlan, can be set this node.

h3cCBQoSNestCfgInfoTable.name: h3cCBQoSNestCfgInfoTable
h3cCBQoSNestCfgInfoTable.description: Insert a service VLAN tag or customer VLAN tag into a packet. A VLAN tag contains the VLAN ID field and the 802.1p priority field. Both the service VLAN ID and the customer VLAN ID can not be set at the same time. One of them must be set. The 802.1p priority of the service VLAN tag and that of the customer VLAN tag can be set optionally. However, both of them can not be set at the same time. The new setting overwrites the previous one.

h3cCBQoSNestServiceVlanID.name: h3cCBQoSNestServiceVlanID

h3cCBQoSApplyObjectIndex.description: QoS apply object index. It represents the unique identifier of QoS policy applied position. It generates when QoS policy is applied considering ifIndex, VLAN ID, ATM PVC, FR DLCI and policy nesting.

h3cCBQoSApplyObjectDirection.name: h3cCBQoSApplyObjectDirection
h3cCBQoSApplyObjectDirection.description: The direction of QoS apply object.

h3cCBQoSApplyObjectMainSite.name: h3cCBQoSApplyObjectMainSite
h3cCBQoSApplyObjectMainSite.description: Its value depends on h3cCBQoSApplyObjectType. It represents VLAN ID When h3cCBQoSApplyObjectType is vlan(2), otherwise it represents ifIndex.

h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubChannel.name: h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubChannel
h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubChannel.description: Its value depends on h3cCBQoSApplyObjectType. It represents the value of VPI/VCI, of which high 16-bits is VPI and low 16-bits is VCI, when h3cCBQoSApplyObjectType is atmPvc(3). It represents the value of data link connection identifier in FR network, when h3cCBQoSApplyObjectType is frDlci(4). Otherwise the value is '0xFFFFFFFF'.

h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubClass.name: h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubClass
h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubClass.description: The value represents level-1 sub class index when the QoS apply object is level-2 or level-3 nesting policy. Otherwise the value is '0xFFFFFFFF'.

h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubClassSec.name: h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubClassSec
h3cCBQoSApplyObjectSubClassSec.description: The value represents level-2 sub class index when the QoS apply object is level-3 nesting policy. Otherwise the value is '0xFFFFFFFF'.

h3cCBQoSIntApplyObjectTable.name: h3cCBQoSIntApplyObjectTable
h3cCBQoSIntApplyObjectTable.description: A table used for querying the QoS apply object indexes by interface index. It is suitable for querying QoS apply object indexes for policies applied on Ethernet ports, ATM ports and FR ports.

h3cCBQoSIntApplyObjectEntry.name: h3cCBQoSIntApplyObjectEntry

h3cCBQoSVlanApplyObjectTable.name: h3cCBQoSVlanApplyObjectTable

If the value of h3cCBQoSVlanApplyObjectVlanID is 0, it means querying Qos apply object index for policy applied on global.
